1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,633
<i>You have no right
to send my guest away!</i>

2
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:13,233
<i>I'll let you talk
to someone I know.</i>

3
00:00:13,367 --> 00:00:16,133
<i> Someone who's not a scammer.</i>

4
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,267
<i> Mom, are you okay?</i>

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,500
<i> I'm just having a stomachache.</i>

6
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:24,300
<i>It's forbidden to talk
to the dead.</i>

7
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:26,533
<i> You have to let her rest.</i>

8
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:30,000
<i>It's like my head
was being split open.</i>

9
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:32,100
<i>That's it, Felma.
We're getting you checked.</i>

10
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:34,967
<i>That's what I was hoping
to ask you.</i>

11
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:38,667
<i>You ask for money
as if I owe you something.</i>

12
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,600
<i> I'll send it.</i>

13
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:42,500
<i>But honestly,
I don't even have to.</i>

14
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,033
<i> I already got what I wanted.</i>

15
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:46,633
<i>Timo already did everything
I told him to do.</i>

16
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:52,267
What do you mean by Timo
follows all of her orders?

17
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:54,600
Son, your mother and I were
right about our suspicions

18
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:55,667
from the very beginning.

19
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:58,467
Hazel bribed Timo

20
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:01,967
into claiming he witnessed
Coleen push Jessica.

21
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:06,033
You know, Dad,
your wife is so evil.

22
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:08,833
Yeah. But I'm ending her
evilness today.

23
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,867
I'm going ahead with my plan.

24
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,200
You have a plan? What plan?

25
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,767
Aside from clearing Coleen
of her case,

26
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:19,267
I went back to Hazel to look
for evidence against her.

27
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:21,200
And once I have it,
I'm going to sue her.

28
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:22,533
After that, I'll push through
with the annulment.

29
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:24,167
Then I'll come back
and be with all of you.

30
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:26,333
But Dad, why didn't you tell us?

31
00:01:26,467 --> 00:01:28,967
Of course, son. Back then,
I had nothing. No proof.

32
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:32,333
But now, I finally have a lead.

33
00:01:32,467 --> 00:01:34,367
That's why I'm telling you this.

34
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:36,400
Because I need your help.

35
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:38,667
Of course, Dad.
Anything you need.

36
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:39,933
Just keep us in the loop, okay?

37
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:42,833
Yes. I will, son.
But don't tell anyone yet.

38
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,667
Especially your mother.

39
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:47,100
How is she, by the way?

40
00:03:03,867 --> 00:03:11,567
Hello? Felma?
Hello, Felma? Felma!

41
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:23,100
Hasn't Diana been discharged
from the hospital?

42
00:03:23,267 --> 00:03:26,000
Son, I pity your wife.

43
00:03:27,267 --> 00:03:31,367
Her sickness keeps getting worse
because of all these problems.

44
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:34,233
I don't know what to do anymore.

45
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,100
No one longer lends me money.

46
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:40,733
Maybe the chairwoman
could lend you?

47
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:42,867
I still owe her.

48
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,367
How about...

49
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:47,167
Aren't you listening?

50
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:52,033
I told you,
no one will lend me anything!

51
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:57,400
I'm sorry, Mom.

52
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:01,167
This is all my fault.

53
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:11,400
What about Ma'am Hazel?
Maybe you should go to her.

54
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:27,633
Son, I don't want to.

55
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,933
She yelled at me over the phone.

56
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:33,933
Diana and I had an agreement
with her.

57
00:04:35,133 --> 00:04:37,667
I did everything she asked me.

58
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,500
She wouldn't abandon
her promise, would she?

59
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:46,033
But I'm scared of Ma'am Hazel.

60
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:47,867
I'm really scared of her.

61
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,367
Just be brave, Mom.

62
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,033
Why is this happening
to you and your wife?

63
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:57,500
To us?

64
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,033
This is my fault.

65
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,733
I shouldn't have surrendered.

66
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:07,367
We should've just gone home
to the province and hid there.

67
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,367
Why is Mom taking so long?

68
00:05:17,533 --> 00:05:20,300
She's just finishing
some paperwork.

69
00:05:20,433 --> 00:05:22,500
But she's been gone a while.

70
00:05:23,967 --> 00:05:25,133
I know.

71
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:29,233
Maybe she's finishing everything
because she has a date later.

72
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:30,433
Date?

73
00:05:31,467 --> 00:05:35,433
I saw Noah leaving your mom's
office earlier.

74
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,867
Then he said,

75
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,433
"See you after lunch."

76
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:43,700
Auntie, come on.

77
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:47,767
Mom only ever loved Dad.

78
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:51,133
There's no way she and Uncle
Noah will get back together.

79
00:05:52,633 --> 00:05:55,167
Well, your dad did leave
your mom again.

80
00:05:55,300 --> 00:06:01,833
Maybe Felma and Noah will try
to work things out again.

81
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:03,100
Who knows.

82
00:06:04,167 --> 00:06:07,200
Mom doesn't love anyone else.

83
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,033
And Uncle Noah knows that.

84
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:10,600
True.

85
00:06:10,733 --> 00:06:12,333
Let's be real.

86
00:06:12,467 --> 00:06:16,600
Your mom's heart still belongs
to your dad.

87
00:06:16,733 --> 00:06:19,800
If she had open-heart surgery
right now,

88
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:23,533
the doctor would see
your dad's name right there.

89
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:27,900
But if I were the doctor,
I'd erase that name immediately.

90
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,233
Ma'am?

91
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:32,233
Is Ma'am Felma here?
I have papers for her to sign.

92
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:35,167
Of course, she's in her office,
right?

93
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:38,000
I checked earlier.
I don't think she's there.

94
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,333
The door's locked.

95
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:42,467
Ma'am Andrea, something might've
happened to Ma'am Felma inside.

96
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:43,700
What?

97
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,567
Wait, excuse me.

98
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:52,033
- Mom?
- Sis?

99
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:54,067
Are you sure she's inside?

100
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:56,867
Yes, Ma'am. I heard her scream,
then something fell.

101
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:57,700
Sis?

102
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,733
Get the spare key
from my office.

103
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:00,800
Okay, Ma'am.

104
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,767
- Sis, open the door!
- Mom?

105
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:06,133
- Ma'am Felma? Felma?
- Mom?

106
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:10,900
- Uncle Noah!
- Felma!

107
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,867
- Mom!
- Felma!

108
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,433
Felma!

109
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:25,667
Move! Move aside!
Arjun, get the car! Hurry!

110
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,767
Mom?

111
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:41,700
Nurse, put it on the bed.

112
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,100
Patient coming through.

113
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:45,833
Nurse?

114
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,000
IV drip.

115
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,667
Mr. Salvador.

116
00:07:55,867 --> 00:07:57,833
We found her unconscious.

117
00:08:00,267 --> 00:08:01,833
We'll take care of her.

118
00:08:01,967 --> 00:08:02,967
Don't worry.

119
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:07,867
Noah...

120
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,133
Noah, does the doctor know you?

121
00:08:11,167 --> 00:08:16,333
And Uncle, why didn't she ask
what happened to Mom?

122
00:08:16,467 --> 00:08:18,233
She already knows what to do.

123
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,900
This is the second time
I've brought your mom here.

124
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,300
Why?

125
00:08:30,567 --> 00:08:31,767
Severe headache.

126
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:32,600
Wait.

127
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,033
You brought her before?

128
00:08:35,167 --> 00:08:37,000
What did the doctor say
the first time?

129
00:08:38,067 --> 00:08:41,467
Noah, is something wrong
with Felma?

130
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,100
The doctor still isn't sure.

131
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,367
She hasn't taken the tests yet.

132
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,233
She said she was okay.

133
00:08:52,633 --> 00:08:54,167
Just stress-related.

134
00:08:57,933 --> 00:09:00,067
But I already brought her here
earlier today.

135
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,033
And then, this.

136
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:15,033
Oximeter.

137
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,367
Blood pressure.

138
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,933
- Yes, Doctor.
- Okay.

139
00:09:21,633 --> 00:09:23,800
Nurse, dextrose.

140
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,667
Who are you?

141
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,167
Sir Manuel?

142
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:21,067
How did you know me?

143
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:24,600
I'm Becca, Timo's mother.

144
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:27,333
I saw you with Ma'am Felma
before,

145
00:10:27,467 --> 00:10:29,900
when she spoke with Diana.

146
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:35,133
Diana told me everything about
who you are

147
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,633
and why you talked to her.

148
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:49,100
Why are you here
at Ma'am Hazel's house?

149
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:53,700
Because Diana didn't listen
to us.

150
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:55,967
She believed Hazel more.

151
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:01,833
Is Ma'am Hazel home?

152
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:04,133
Can I talk to her?

153
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,967
She's asleep.

154
00:11:12,100 --> 00:11:14,833
I know why you're here.

155
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:18,533
You're here for the support
Hazel promised Diana,

156
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:21,267
so Timo will take back his
statement.

157
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:25,733
Miss Becca, is that all Hazel
told your son to do?

158
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:31,100
Or did she also tell Timo
to accuse Coleen?

159
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:35,267
I know you need the money.

160
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,300
I can talk to Felma.

161
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:40,467
Tell her to restore
the 300,000-peso offer.

162
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,367
Just tell the truth.

163
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:47,767
Please, Miss Becca.
I'm begging you.

164
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:51,867
Tell the truth so I can get out
of here.

165
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:54,267
So I can go back to my family.

166
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,800
Miss Becca!

167
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:07,400
Miss Becca!

168
00:12:07,533 --> 00:12:09,167
Perfect timing.

169
00:12:09,300 --> 00:12:11,367
I was just on my way
to you and Diana

170
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,967
to give the support money
for the kids.

171
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:16,033
Sorry if I'm a little late.

172
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,633
There's just so much
to take care of.

173
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:21,733
Actually, I'm heading
to my friend's place after.

174
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:23,267
Want to come with me?

175
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:26,067
I'll buy things for the kids,
your grandkids.

176
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,567
No...

177
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:28,500
no, that's okay.

178
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:30,433
No? Manuel, want to come?

179
00:12:30,567 --> 00:12:31,833
No, you two go ahead.

180
00:12:31,967 --> 00:12:33,400
You sure?

181
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,633
Come on,

182
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,533
let's go.

183
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:42,700
Let's go shopping.
We'll buy things for the kids.

184
00:12:51,233 --> 00:12:55,000
Miss Felma, when was your
last executive checkup?

185
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:01,433
Early last year?

186
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:05,267
Or maybe the year before?

187
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,800
I...

188
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:08,700
I can't remember.

189
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:12,933
I suggest you undergo
an executive checkup

190
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:14,600
as soon as you can.

191
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:19,200
So we can determine the cause
of your frequent headaches.

192
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,567
Can she do it tomorrow, Doctor?

193
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:23,667
Yes.

194
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,200
Tomorrow is fine.

195
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:29,300
Doctor, it's just my head
hurting.

196
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:32,867
Felma,

197
00:13:34,033 --> 00:13:35,933
could you please listen
to the doctor?

198
00:13:36,967 --> 00:13:39,333
Get the checkup done.

199
00:13:39,467 --> 00:13:41,000
You're already here anyway.

200
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:45,600
Let's find out if everything
is really okay with you.

201
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:51,233
Mom, listen to Uncle Noah.
He's right.

202
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,867
Sis, don't be stubborn.

203
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,933
Just listen, okay?

204
00:13:59,833 --> 00:14:01,967
Okay. All right, Doc.

205
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:04,533
Okay.
We'll arrange it for tomorrow.

206
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:11,533
<i> How's Mom?</i>

207
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,767
You're really hardheaded, Becca,
you know that?

208
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:30,400
What are you doing here?

209
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:32,367
What were you and Manuel talking
about?

210
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:36,100
Nothing, Ma'am.

211
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:38,433
We didn't talk about anything.

212
00:14:38,567 --> 00:14:41,467
I had just arrived
when you stepped out.

213
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,700
You'd better make sure.

214
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:47,400
You know what could happen
to Timo

215
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:50,533
if I don't like what you said or
if you and Diana try anything.

216
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:51,467
Am I clear?

217
00:14:59,967 --> 00:15:02,033
When we reach the gate,
you get off.

218
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,300
Go home.
Don't come back here again.

219
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:13,567
Just a thousand pesos?

220
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:16,800
That's not what you
and Diana agreed on.

221
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:21,600
I'll add more. Just wait!

222
00:15:28,867 --> 00:15:29,700
Dad.

223
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:30,833
<i> Son.</i>

224
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:33,667
<i>Becca, Timo's mother,
came earlier.</i>

225
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,300
<i>I talked to her, and it looked
like she was about to confess.</i>

226
00:15:36,467 --> 00:15:38,200
<i> Then Hazel showed up.</i>

227
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,433
Oh, too bad.

228
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:41,733
<i> Exactly.</i>

229
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:44,933
I don't think she'll talk
anymore now

230
00:15:45,067 --> 00:15:47,767
that she saw Hazel with me.

231
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,333
So what do we do?

232
00:15:49,467 --> 00:15:51,067
<i> Listen.</i>

233
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,800
Go to Timo.

234
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:56,167
Tell him we're willing
to help him,

235
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:58,233
as long as he tells us
everything Hazel

236
00:15:58,367 --> 00:15:59,067
ordered him to do.

237
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:00,333
<i> Okay, Dad.</i>

238
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:03,367
Hopefully, he talks, right?
So Hazel can finally be charged.

239
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:08,567
And so we can tell Coleen
the truth.

240
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:13,367
What truth?

241
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,833
What truth, Jeff?

242
00:16:20,967 --> 00:16:23,033
Are you hiding something
from me?

243
00:16:23,167 --> 00:16:25,367
<i> And who were you talking to?</i>

244
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,333
What are you keeping from me?

245
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,667
Okay, okay.

246
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:32,600
Yes.

247
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:37,333
<i> I gave Dad a secret phone.</i>

248
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:39,700
<i> Yeah.</i>

249
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:43,033
I gave him a phone,
and we hid it,

250
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:44,100
especially from you.

251
00:16:44,233 --> 00:16:45,700
Because, Coleen, we know you.

252
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:48,433
You can't keep yourself
from calling Dad.

253
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:51,500
Then Hazel might catch him.
What will happen then?

254
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:56,567
Hello, Dad?

255
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:57,400
Sweetheart?

256
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:59,000
<i> Dad, how are you?</i>

257
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:01,333
Hazel isn't hurting you, is she?

258
00:17:01,467 --> 00:17:04,267
No, I will no longer let her.

259
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,800
Dad, I miss you.

260
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:09,333
I miss you so much, too, dear.

261
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,767
Is your mother there?

262
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:13,600
She's in the hospital, Dad.

263
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:14,833
<i> What?</i>

264
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,800
<i> Why is she in the hospital?</i>

265
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:20,000
Dad...

266
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:23,867
<i> She just had a checkup.</i>

267
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,500
Her head was hurting.

268
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:27,700
But she's okay now.

269
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,133
Yes, Dad.

270
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:31,567
Thankfully, she was brought
to the hospital quickly

271
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,133
when she collapsed at work.

272
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:35,033
<i> She collapsed?</i>

273
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:37,333
<i>Jeffrey, why didn't you tell me?</i>

274
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:44,100
Dad, she just lost her balance,
that's all.

275
00:17:44,233 --> 00:17:48,467
Good thing Uncle Noah was in
the office when it happened.

276
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:50,500
He rushed her to the hospital.

277
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:52,133
She's with Noah?

278
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:55,600
Dad, don't worry.
She's fine now.

279
00:17:55,733 --> 00:17:57,400
Andrea called.

280
00:17:57,533 --> 00:17:58,933
Mom's okay.

281
00:17:59,067 --> 00:18:00,167
<i> All right, son.</i>

282
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,433
But for things like this,
tell me right away, okay?

283
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:05,933
Manuel, I brought dinner.

284
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:09,367
Okay, I'll call again later.
Hazel's here.

285
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:17,567
See? Look at your mouth.
You almost got us in trouble.

286
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:20,767
Why don't you want Dad to know
what really happened?

287
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:23,500
Sweetie, Dad has enough on his
mind already.

288
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,033
Let's not add to it.

289
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:26,767
He'll just worry even more.

290
00:18:32,267 --> 00:18:33,433
Ma'am, NPO.

291
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:37,567
After 10 PM, no eating
or drinking anything.

292
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:40,567
You need 10 to 12 hours
of fasting

293
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:42,467
for tomorrow's blood test.

294
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:47,467
What other tests
will they run on me?

295
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,800
Aside from the blood test,
or Chem 8,

296
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:51,367
there's also a physical exam.

297
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:55,600
That includes urinalysis,
fecalysis, X-ray, ECG,

298
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:58,100
and a head CT scan.

299
00:18:58,233 --> 00:18:59,400
That many?

300
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:02,167
If the tests show any
abnormalities,

301
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:06,000
they might be connected
to your recurring headaches.

302
00:19:08,367 --> 00:19:10,467
You should go home for now.

303
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,500
Just come back for me tomorrow.

304
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,433
No, Mom. I'll stay with you.

305
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:18,933
Me, too. I'll stay.

306
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:21,400
You two have nothing
to do here anyway.

307
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:23,267
And I'll just be sleeping.

308
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:24,433
But Mom...

309
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:25,833
No more insisting.

310
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:26,933
Go home.

311
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:29,100
I'll stay.

312
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:30,467
You...

313
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,333
don't argue with me.

314
00:19:34,533 --> 00:19:37,033
All right. But I'm coming back
tomorrow, okay?

315
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:44,500
Mom, you're going to be okay.

316
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:47,533
Just don't be stubborn, okay?

317
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:55,867
Wait, so Uncle Manuel
has another plan?

318
00:19:57,933 --> 00:19:59,067
Yeah, bro.

319
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:02,100
Dad's looking for evidence
against Hazel.

320
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:05,400
He really wants Hazel
to end up in jail,

321
00:20:05,533 --> 00:20:07,533
so he can come back to us.

322
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:10,033
Are you the only one
who knows about his plan?

323
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,900
And you're telling me now?

324
00:20:12,033 --> 00:20:13,067
Yeah. Why?

325
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,133
Unbelievable.

326
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:17,933
I might end up telling
your sister Andrea again.

327
00:20:18,067 --> 00:20:19,800
Bro, I really need your help
right now.

328
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:21,900
And you have to keep it
to yourself, okay?

329
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:23,267
You're so manly.
Stop acting like a gossip.

330
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,200
Totally doesn't suit you.
Endure it.

331
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:26,667
Fine, fine. I'm in.

332
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,933
So, what does Uncle Manuel
need help with?

333
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:40,733
Talk to Diana and your mom.

334
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,800
Tell them not to rush me.

335
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:45,833
What do they think I am, an ATM?

336
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:49,033
But Ma'am, we had an agreement.

337
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:52,667
You're all the same.

338
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,333
Impatient.

339
00:20:54,467 --> 00:20:55,733
Money-hungry.

340
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:59,233
Enough with the insults, Ma'am.

341
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:00,733
We already talked.

342
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:03,633
I fulfilled what I promised you.

343
00:21:04,700 --> 00:21:07,133
You should fulfill
what you promised me.

344
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:09,500
If you don't...

345
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:10,367
And if I don't, what?

346
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:11,600
I'll talk.

347
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:16,167
I'll tell them everything
you ordered me to do.

348
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:18,100
Are you threatening me?

349
00:21:19,267 --> 00:21:20,700
Go on.

350
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:21,933
Try it.

351
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,833
You think anyone will believe
you?

352
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:30,233
You really don't think something
bad can happen to you in here,

353
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:31,033
do you?

354
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:34,000
Not just to you...

355
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:35,667
But to your family.

356
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,167
What?

357
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,567
Are you challenging me?

358
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:53,300
That's it.

359
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,167
Good.

360
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:57,967
Keep quiet.

361
00:21:59,133 --> 00:22:00,667
Shut your mouth.

362
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:08,100
So everybody stays happy,
especially your kids.

363
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:18,833
Jeffrey Cruz, Sir.

364
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:21,367
We'll be visiting
Timothy Malabanan.

365
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:24,033
Walk-ins aren't allowed.
You need a request.

366
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,867
No, Sir. We have a letter
from Colonel Sarabia.

367
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,167
We'll be quick, too.

368
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:31,800
Okay. But wait here first.
Malabanan has another visitor.

369
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,267
Let me just check the time.

370
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,833
I'm still here.

371
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:38,100
We just finished talking.

372
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:40,267
I don't like his tone at all.

373
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:42,367
Yes.

374
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:47,100
It's Hazel! It's her!

375
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:49,500
Hey!

376
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,267
Hey, kid!

377
00:22:56,967 --> 00:22:58,000
Hey!

378
00:22:58,133 --> 00:22:59,267
Really now!

379
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,067
You even stole the umbrella?

380
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,233
Kids here are really
mischievous.

381
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:05,200
Ma'am, I'm so sorry.
The kids are just playful.

382
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:06,433
Apologies.

383
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:11,767
That was close.

384
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:14,033
Yeah.

385
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:16,600
Sir?

386
00:23:18,133 --> 00:23:21,267
They won't know we visited
Malabanan, right?

387
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,133
Don't worry.

388
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:23,833
Our visitors' log
is confidential.

389
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,100
<i>Do you think anyone
will believe you?</i>

390
00:23:38,233 --> 00:23:42,500
<i>You really don't think something
bad could happen to you in here,</i>

391
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:43,233
<i> do you?</i>

392
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,300
<i> Not just you...</i>

393
00:23:44,433 --> 00:23:46,033
<i> But your whole family.</i>

394
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:49,633
<i>Honestly, Your Honor,
before all of this,</i>

395
00:23:49,767 --> 00:23:51,667
<i>they were very close
to each other.</i>

396
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:56,333
I'm Jeffrey Cruz.

397
00:23:57,433 --> 00:23:58,300
I know.

398
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,533
Coleen's sibling.

399
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:02,667
I know you.

400
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,500
Timo, I just want to ask you
something.

401
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:15,800
<i>Shut your mouth so everybody
stays happy.</i>

402
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:19,800
<i> Especially your kids.</i>

403
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:23,767
Enough already!

404
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,700
Why are you here?

405
00:24:25,833 --> 00:24:27,667
You won't get anything from me.

406
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:31,300
Timo, why are you talking
to Hazel?

407
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:35,167
Don't deny it. We saw her.

408
00:24:37,767 --> 00:24:39,467
Timo, is Hazel threatening you?

409
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,967
Threatening your life?
Your family's life?

410
00:24:44,667 --> 00:24:47,100
Just tell us the truth.
We'll help you.

411
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:51,567
Really, Timo.

412
00:24:52,867 --> 00:24:54,933
We promise we'll help you.

413
00:24:55,067 --> 00:24:58,600
I can't risk my family's life.

414
00:25:05,500 --> 00:25:08,567
This is your CT scan report,
Miss Felma.

415
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:10,833
I have a brain tumor, Doc?

416
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:15,167
Noah, I don't want anyone
to know about this yet.

417
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:17,200
Timo, don't be afraid
to tell us.

418
00:25:17,333 --> 00:25:19,833
If you want the truth,
come back tomorrow.

419
00:25:19,967 --> 00:25:20,833
Wow...

420
00:25:20,967 --> 00:25:22,667
what a coincidence.

421
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,267
Mind if we share a table?

422
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,600
No!
